com.bmd.jrt.channel

Interface ParameterChannel<INPUT,OUTPUT>

  • Type Parameters:
    INPUT - the input data type.
    OUTPUT - the output data type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Channel, InputChannel<INPUT>

    public interface ParameterChannel<INPUT,OUTPUT>
extends InputChannel<INPUT>
    Interface defining a parameter input channel, that is the channel used to pass input data to the routine invocation.

    Created by davide on 9/15/14.

        @Nonnull
ParameterChannel<INPUT,OUTPUT> after(@Nonnull
                                           TimeDuration delay)
        Description copied from interface: InputChannel
        Tells the channel to delay the transfer of data of the specified time duration.
        Note that an abort execution will be delayed as well. Note, however, that a delayed abort will not prevent the invocation to complete, as input data do.
        Specified by:
        after in interface InputChannel<INPUT>
        Parameters:
        delay - the delay.
        Returns:
        this channel.

ParameterChannel<INPUT,OUTPUT> pass(@Nullable
                                          OutputChannel<INPUT> channel)
        Description copied from interface: InputChannel
        Passes the specified channel to this one.

        Note that this channel will be bound as a result of the call, thus preventing any other reader to get data from the output channel.
